**who —** Quantum Error Correction — a frontier sphere

**what —** Qubits forget. They decohere, you can't copy them, and looking destroys them — so the trick that makes quantum computing possible is hiding one perfect 'logical' qubit inside many flawed physical ones, and measuring the errors without ever reading the data.

